    <h1>Exploring XML and JavaScript</h1>
    
    <h2>What is XML?</h2>
    <p>XML, or eXtensible Markup Language, is a versatile markup language designed to store and transport data in a structured format.</p>

    <h2>How is XML used?</h2>
    <p>XML finds its applications in various domains including web services, configuration files, data exchange between different platforms, and more.</p>

    <h2>What does XML look like? (Example)</h2>
    <pre>
        <code>
            &lt;bookstore&gt;
                &lt;book category="fiction"&gt;
                    &lt;title&gt;Harry Potter&lt;/title&gt;
                    &lt;author&gt;J.K. Rowling&lt;/author&gt;
                    &lt;year&gt;2005&lt;/year&gt;
                    &lt;price&gt;29.99&lt;/price&gt;
                &lt;/book&gt;
            &lt;/bookstore&gt;
        </code>
    </pre>

    <h2>What is JavaScript?</h2>
    <p>JavaScript is a powerful scripting language used to create dynamic and interactive web content.</p>

    <h2>How is JavaScript related to HTML and CSS?</h2>
    <p>JavaScript works in conjunction with HTML and CSS to provide enhanced functionality and interactivity to web pages. HTML defines the structure, CSS styles the presentation, and JavaScript adds behavior.</p>

    <h2>Common JavaScript elements, properties, methods, and functions</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Elements: Variables, arrays, objects</li>
        <li>Properties: length property of an array</li>
        <li>Methods: push() method of an array</li>
        <li>Functions: setTimeout() function</li>
    </ul>

